			<h1 class="purple-light">Resources for Educators</h1>
			<br/>
			<p class="ref"><a href="https://www.cdc.gov/ncbddd/autism/educator.html">Autism Spectrum Disorder</a></p>
			<p>This source contains information for educators about Autism Spectrum Disorder including facts about the disorder and numerous links to other informational and supportive websites.</p>

			<p class="ref"><a href="https://www.naset.org/">National Association of Special Education Teachers</a></p>
			<p>The National Association of Special Education Teachers website is full of excellent articles and resources, not just about ASD but a variety of other disabilities as well.</p>

			<p class="ref"><a href="https://www.isbe.net/pages/special-education-programs.aspx">Illinois State Board of Education</a></p>
			<p>The Illinois State Board of Education website outlines special education programs in our state and effectively explains different aspects of the special education process.</p>

			<p class="ref"><a href="https://www.isbe.net/pages/learning-standards.aspx">Illinois Learning Standards</a></p>
			<p>Within their website, ISBE also provides essential information pertaining to the Illinois learning standards. This website can be a vital tool when planning curriculum for your classroom. This resource describes key concepts and content that all students are expected to know upon completing their education.</p>

			<p class="ref"><a href="https://www.iidc.indiana.edu/styles/iidc/defiles/IRCA/CommunicationCurriculum2018.pdf">Indiana Resource Center for Autism</a></p>
			<p>This link includes a detailed curriculum targeted towards students with ASD. This guide can serve as a helpful resource when creating social communication curriculum. It has lots of wonderful activities and ideas!</p>

			<p class="ref"><a href="https://www.ocali.org/up_doc/Standards-Based-Life-Skills-Curriculum.pdf">Standards-Based Life Skills Cirriculum</a></p>
			<p>This is a fantastic resource that contains a curriculum guide for life skills programs. It includes activities that incorporate and fulfill educational standards.</p>

			<p class="ref"><a href="https://education.wm.edu/centers/ttac/resources/articles/inclusion/effectiveteach/">Effective Teaching Practices for Students in Inclusive Classrooms</a></p>
			<p>This article describes various teaching practices that are effective in fostering successful inclusion environments. The strategies outlined in this article are all researched based and the author does a great job of describing their usefulness as well as provide explanations as to how to best integrate these practices within your own classroom.</p>

			<p class="ref"><a href="https://www.brighthubeducation.com/special-ed-inclusion-strategies/66075-inclusion-strategies-and-techniques-for-mainstreaming-special-ed-students/">Inclusion Strategies for Mainstreamed Classrooms</a></p>
			<p>This link is a nice guide for both general education teachers as well as special education teachers. It talks about numerous techniques and strategies for promoting inclusion.</p>

			<p class="ref"><a href="https://www.iidc.indiana.edu/pages/evidence-based-practices-for-effective-communication-and-social-intervention">Evidence-Based Practices for Effective Communication and Social Intervention</a></p>
			<p>This link is a nice guide for both general education teachers as well as special education teachers. It talks about numerous techniques and strategies for promoting inclusion.</p>

